liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Fullback Charnze Nicoll-Klokstad gets the opening try, but it's on the back of a perfectly weighted pass by that man, Shaun Johnson. He shaped to go long to the wing, but held it up and went short to his fullback to send him through a small gap between Bradman Best and Greg Marzhew. Adam Pompey misses the conversion from out wide, but what a start for the home side.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: THE WARRIORS SCORE IN THE SECOND MINUTE!!

children.content: Fullback Charnze Nicoll-Klokstad gets the opening try, but it's on the back of a perfectly weighted pass by that man, Shaun Johnson.
He shaped to go long to the wing, but held it up and went short to his fullback to send him through a small gap between Bradman Best and Greg Marzhew.
Adam Pompey misses the conversion from out wide, but what a start for the home side.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Newcastle gets possession first, and Jacob Saifiti is almost dragged into touch on the first hit-up! That might have blown this stadium apart if it happened. But next best thing for the Warriors, with Greg Marzhew knocking on two tackles later. Warriors on the attack from 30 metres out.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 1' This semifinal is off and running

children.content: Newcastle gets possession first, and Jacob Saifiti is almost dragged into touch on the first hit-up! That might have blown this stadium apart if it happened.
But next best thing for the Warriors, with Greg Marzhew knocking on two tackles later.
Warriors on the attack from 30 metres out.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Warriors' inspirational and practical leader has been missing for the past two weeks, including their big loss to Penrith in the first week of the finals. But now, Shaun Johnson is back. Who knows how well his injured calf will hold up (it was strapped at training this week) but his presence is huge for this team, who have struggled in attack without him. Both teams are basically 1-17, although as confirmed in the 24-hour updates, the Knights have elevated 18th man Brodie Jones onto the bench in place of Daniel Saifiti, who is out with a hamstring injury.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Shaun Johnson is in the Warriors' number seven jersey

children.content: The Warriors' inspirational and practical leader has been missing for the past two weeks, including their big loss to Penrith in the first week of the finals.
Who knows how well his injured calf will hold up (it was strapped at training this week) but his presence is huge for this team, who have struggled in attack without him.

Both teams are basically 1-17, although as confirmed in the 24-hour updates, the Knights have elevated 18th man Brodie Jones onto the bench in place of Daniel Saifiti, who is out with a hamstring injury.
